🆕 __Build Challenge__   


🌹Roses are red, :lapis_lazuli: Lapis is Blue. We love gardening, how about you? Do you have dreams of building the fanciest of gardens? Your wish has come true. Build and share a Fancy Garden!

Create a fancy, relaxing garden to enjoy any day of the year!

🌻Fancy Garden - February 7th to February 21st

📄 __Guidelines:__
:earth: Must be built in Minecraft Earth
:loading: This should be a brand new build and not be something that you've already built
:grass_block:  Build plate size will not matter & won't be a factor in judging
:mining: Feel free to ask for advice pertaining to your build in #fancy-garden-challenge 
:mob_of_me: All work must be done by one individual
:fast_parrot: Remember, this is for fun only
📌If it's a submission picture, please feel free to ask a moderator to pin it.
:sign: __Winning submissions may be used in social media__ :friends:

Here I present my build for the #fancy-garden-challenge 

I made it fancy by adding some classy classical music - *The Flower Duet* from the opera *Lakmé* by Delibes. Because it's me, it's also kinda cheesy....

Filming this one was a challenge, to say the least. Too many Mobs of Me would cause lag, and it was hilarious watching them all interact in the confined settings of the maze. I took out *Demon-Spawn Child from Hell* for being mean to the pig, and *Dodgy-Looking Tradesman Guy* for constantly stalking the pig in a creepy manner... I feel like I could make a documentary from the out-takes and off-cuts...

In the end, I settled on *Purple Joan Collins* and *Albino Faceless Linda Evans* as the Muddy Pigs co-stars, first facing off with each other, then ganging up on the pig. They did not disappoint.
